/*!
    \fn int add(int a, int b)
    \brief Adds two numbers together.

    This method accepts \a a and \a b arguments to return an integer value.
    Use \c add() to perform addition. The result is \b important.
*/

/*!
    \fn void format(double value)
    \brief Formats a value for display using all inline markup styles.

    The parameter \a value is formatted according to the current locale.

    Rendering variants for the same content:
    \b {bold via backslash-b}, \bold {bold via backslash-bold},
    \e {italic via backslash-e}, \i {italic via backslash-i},
    \underline {underlined text}, \tt {teletype font},
    \c {inline code}, \sub {subscript}, \sup {superscript}.

    UI references use \uicontrol {File > Save}.\br
    Trademark example: Qt \tm is a registered trademark.\br
    Truncated sequences end with \dots

    \sa add(), subtract()
*/
